column3: Unique identifier for each individual shell. The first number (1-5) refers to the experiment number, the second (1-3) to the replicate number, the third (1-11) refers to the taxon, and the fourth (1-6) to the set of samples it is grouped with.
Unique identifier for each experiment. The first letter refers to the type of study while the number refers to the individual experiment.
Scientific name of taxon of individual shell.
The bag from which each individual shell was sourced.
The pocket in which each shell was randomly placed. Varies from 1-11 to 1-5 based on the number of shells sampled.
The date and time at which the experiment was started. Rounded to the nearest minute.
The date and time at which the experiment was finished. Rounded to the nearest minute.
The mass of each individual measured before experimental treatment.
The mass of each individual measured after experimental treatment.
Rough three-dimensional shape of the shell.
surface area as calculated in imageJ from image 1 of specimen
surface area as calculated in imageJ from image 2 of specimen
type of calcium carbonate (Calcite or Aragonite)
magnesium content percentage based on XRD findings
notes on damaged/lost shells for exclusion
column to indicate exclusion of shells for reasons denoted in 'notes' column. 0 = include, 1=exclude.
